    {
      "beat_id": "B02",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "Start with two uncoupled states. As an external parameter changes, one energy rises and the other falls. With no communication between them, the lines cross cleanly.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "trace"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B02.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.81,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B02.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T14:11:05"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B03",
      "estimated_duration_s": 9,
      "narration_text": "Now add a perturbation that connects the states. Away from the meeting point, the effect is small because the energy separation is large.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "accumulate"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B03.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.06,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B03.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T14:11:05"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B04",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "Near the meeting point, the separation shrinks. Mixing becomes strong, and neither state can remain the original pure state.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "merge"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B04.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 7.21,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B04.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T14:11:05"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B05",
      "estimated_duration_s": 7,
      "narration_text": "The closer the bare levels come, the more strongly the coupled energies split.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "split"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B05.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 4.89,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B05.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T14:11:05"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B06",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "The lower eigenvalue bends downward while the upper one bends upward. At closest approach, the gap is twice the magnitude of the coupling g.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "split"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B06.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.15,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B06.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T14:11:05"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B07",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "This is an avoided crossing: the energy curves do not touch, even though the uncoupled reference lines would have crossed at the center.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "compare"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B07.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 7.49,
